        </div>
      </div></div>

      <div class="tile_thumbnail asha_enroll"><div class="tile-wrapper">
        <div class="tile_thumbnail_image">
          <%= image_tag "case_studies/asha_tile_enroll.png", "alt" => "Open Enrollment Drop-In Sessions" %>
        </div>
        <div class="headline">
          <span class="text">Open Enrollment Drop-In Sessions</span>
        </div>
      </div></div>
      
      <div class="tile_thumbnail asha_goal"><div class="tile-wrapper">
        <div class="tile_thumbnail_image">
          <%= image_tag "case_studies/asha_tile_goal.png", "alt" => "Mark your learning goal complete!" %>
        </div>
        <div class="headline">
          <span class="text">Mark your learning goal complete!</span>
        </div>
      </div></div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="large-8 large-centered columns">
      <h2>“It’s easy to use and looks professional.”</h2>
      <p>Two months after launching the Milton Cat Safety Board, over 94% of their target audience has joined. Each week, David and his team take 20 minutes to create safety tiles around various safety topics. The response has been overwhelmingly positive, with 75% of participants reading the tiles each week. As one Field Service Supervisor put it in an unprompted email to David, "This new website is great. I like the points and the friend thing, having fun with it!”</p>

      <h2>Safety Brief Completion Has Increased.</h2>
      <p>For David, the most important thing has been outcomes. Weekly Safety Brief completion has increased by 50% since launch. Prior to using H.Engage, Supervisors could at any given time be a month behind on discussing weekly safety messages and there was no way to track it. David is now able to track who is completing their safety talks with their employees, and is able follow-up with those who are not. This helps Milton CAT continue to create a safe work environment for their employees.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


